.\" Man page for lob-decode
.TH LOB-DECODE 1 "April 2026" "libobsh 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lob-decode \- Reconstruct a file from a Library coordinate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lob-decode
.I coord-file
.I output-file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lob-decode
reads a \fI.coord\fR file (created by \fBlob-encode\fR) and reconstructs
the original file.
.PP
The tool automatically detects whether the coordinate points to a
single page or a multi‑page manifest, and reconstructs the original
file in either case.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B lob-decode script.sh.coord recovered.sh
Reconstructs the original script.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lob-encode (1),
.BR lob-run (1)
